        "subject": "LU-19506 nodemap: appended filesets must consider alt filesets",
        "message": "LU-19506 nodemap: appended filesets must consider alt filesets\n\nWhen mounting a subdirectory, several mounting rules are in place that\nhandle matching a subdirectory to the correct fileset. Here, the man\npage for \"lctl nodemap_fileset_add\" states case 4: \"If fileset matches\nin 3, the presented mounting subdirectory is appended to the primary\nfileset.\"\n\nHowever, this results in the read-only flag not being considered if\nthe appended fileset now matches a read-only alternate fileset. For\ninstance, for the fileset configuration\n1. /dir\n2. /dir/subdir (ro)\nit is possible to mount \"...:/FSNAME/subdir\", which appends \"subdir\"\nto the primary fileset, resulting in the subdirectory \"/dir/subdir\".\nCurrently, no other fileset is considered, but, in such a case, the\nalt fileset imposes read-only restrictions. Therefore, alt filesets\nshould be considered in case 4 of the mounting rules for filesets.\n\nThis patch addresses this issue and modifies sanity-sec test_27e to\ntest this case.\n\nFixes: e899baa2b2 (\"LU-18357 ptlrpc: Add read-only flag for nodemap filesets\")\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-sec\nSigned-off-by: Marc Vef <mvef@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I0e6531a09b78595fc2c9e1f55c9a9bcf6617a73a\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62425\nReviewed-by: Sebastien Buisson <sbuisson@ddn.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
